@host = http://localhost:8080

### 1. Health Check (Public)
GET {{host}}/health
Accept: application/json

### 2. Auth: Register New User
POST {{host}}/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "testuser",
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "Password123!"
}

### 3. Auth: Login to get JWT (Screenshot this for Auth logic)
# @name login
POST {{host}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "testuser",
  "password": "Password123!"
}

@token = {{login.response.body.token}}

### 4. Create a Post (RMM Level 2 - POST - Success 201)
POST {{host}}/api/posts
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "authorId": "user_001",
  "content": "Hello PulseNet! This is a TDD-tested post.",
  "tags": ["dotnet", "microservices"]
}

### 5. Get Recent Posts (RMM Level 2 - GET - Success 200)
GET {{host}}/api/posts/recent
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 6. Update a Post (RMM Level 2 - PUT - Success 200)
# Replace {id} with an ID from the GET response
PUT {{host}}/api/posts/65f...
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "content": "Updated content via Gateway!",
  "tags": ["updated"]
}

### 7. Delete a Post (RMM Level 2 - DELETE - Success 204)
# Replace {id} with an ID from the GET response
DELETE {{host}}/api/posts/65f...
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 8. Test Unauthorized Access (Security Check - Expect 401)
GET {{host}}/api/posts/recent
# No token provided here

### 9. Test Not Found (RMM Level 2 - GET - Expect 404)
GET {{host}}/api/posts/non-existing-id
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}